  "question_id": "9a445136-b125-4dd4-8ef1-46ff96737d45",
  "short_text": "Butterfly",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print a **Butterfly** of `(2 * N) - 1` rows using stars (`*`).\n\n````\n*         * \n* *     * *  \n* * * * * * \n* *     * * \n*         *\n````\n\n<MultiLineNote>\nThere is a space after every star (`*`).\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `(2 * N) - 1` rows containing stars (`*`) as a **Butterfly** shown in the sample output.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 4`, \n\n- Print the stars (`*`) on **7** rows `((2 * 4) - 1)` as shown in the given image.\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-butterfly.png' widthPercent='70'/>\n\n<MultiLineNote>\n\nIn the given image,\n\n- The Empty box indicates the two spaces (\"&nbsp;&nbsp;\").\n- The Star in the box indicates the star and a space (\"* \")\n\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n*             * \n* *         * * \n* * *     * * * \n* * * * * * * * \n* * *     * * * \n* *         * * \n*             *\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "8149c584-e9b1-4780-809e-bb5a085db0b4",
      "code_content": "number = int(input())\n\nfor each_number in range(1, number + 1):\n    stars = \"* \" * each_number\n    spaces = \"  \" * (2 * (number - each_number))\n    each_row = stars + spaces + stars\n    print(each_row)\n    \nfor each_number in range(1, number):\n    stars = \"* \" * (number - each_number)\n    spaces = \"  \" * (2 * each_number)\n    each_row = stars + spaces + stars\n    print(each_row)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
